<div id="challenge-desc" class="box--border--blue box--goal">
    <p i18n-data="ch09~Keep your file up to date by pulling in changes from collaborators."></p>
</div>

<div class="box--solid--light">
    <h2 i18n-data="ch09~Pulling from a Remote"></h3>
    <p i18n-type="standard_html"
        i18n-data="ch09~If you're working on something with someone else you need to stay up to date with the latest changes. So you'll want to {/str/}pull{/str_e/} in any changes that may have been pushed to the central GitHub repository."></p>

    <figure>
        <img class="img_pull" src="../../assets/imgs/pull.png"
            alt="A diagram shows a computer pulling information down from a repository's website">
        <figcaption i18n-type="standard_html" i18n-data="ch09~If someone else {/str/}pushed{/str_e/} changes to the {/str/}remote{/str_e/} repository (on GitHub), you might want to {/str/}pull{/str_e/} these changes into your {/str/}local{/str_e/} repository."></figcaption>
    </figure>
</div>

<div class="box--border--blue box--step">
    <h3 i18n-data="ch09~What has Reporobot been up to?"></h3>
    <p i18n-data="ch09~See if Reporobot has made any changes to your branch by pulling in any changes from the remote named 'origin' on GitHub:"></p>

    <div class='code'><code class="shell">git pull &lt;REMOTENAME&gt; &lt;BRANCHNAME&gt;</code></div>

    <p i18n-data="ch09~If nothing's changed, it will tell you 'Already up-to-date'. If there are changes, Git will merge those changes into your local version."></p>

    <p i18n-data="ch09~Did Reporobot make changes? Git tells you where changes were made. You can open that file and see Reporobot's updates. Surprise, Reporobot is an artist!"></p>
</div>

{{{ verify_directory_button }}}

<div class="box--border--grey box--tip">
    <ul class="no-list-style">
        <li>
            <strong i18n-data="ch09~Check Git status"></strong>
            <div class='code'><code class="shell">git status</code></div>
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong i18n-data="ch09~Pull in changes from a remote branch"></strong>
            <div class='code'><code class="shell">git pull &lt;REMOTENAME&gt; &lt;REMOTEBRANCH&gt;</code></div>
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong i18n-data="ch09~See changes to the remote before you pull in"></strong>
            <div class='code'><code class="shell">git fetch --dry-run</code></div>
        </li>
    </ul>
</div>
